Kingsville Ballpark
April 24 at 10:44 AM ·

In case you missed it last week we are lighting up the Kingsville Ballpark again tonight. We will be joining schools around the country by turning on the ballpark lights on Friday nights through May 8 at 8:20pm, which is 20:20 military time. We will be leaving the lights on for 20 minutes and 20 seconds to honor the class of 2020. We are proud of your accomplishments!

Community members are encouraged to join the movement by turning on their front porch lights in sync with the ballpark lights.

*CDC guidelines remain in effect. Please do no gather at the ballpark.

post_text:
I know this is a difficult situation for our students and parents as well. Everyday I am concerned about academics and events students are missing. There are likely many questions that can’t be answered at the moment or at least until we get started with this temporary way of operating as a school district. I very much appreciate your patience as a valued student or parent. I also can not thank the entire staff enough for their commitment to be ready for any challenge that the coming days and weeks may bring in an effort to still prioritize the well-being and education of our students during this difficult time. Our educational team is working diligently to supply answers to the many questions that have arisen from COVID-19 and our school closure. Within the next few days the website will be updated to provide additional information, including the contacts for questions you may still have. At this time the buildings remain closed. Once again thank you for your patience.

Sincerely,

Lorna Warren
Kingsville R-1 Superintendent

post_text:
The Kingsville R-1 School District is now accepting letters of interest to fill an open position on the School Board. Qualified persons interested in the position may send a letter of interest to Lorna Warren, Superintendent, 101 East Adriatic, Kingsville Missouri 64061.

Membership to the board is open to residents of the Kingsville R-1 School District who have resided in the state for one year prior to the election, and are at least 24 years of age. Candidates must be citizens of the United States and resident taxpayers of the District.

The District will accept letters of interest until September 27, 2019. The open position will serve until the April school board election.

post_text:
KINDERGARTEN ROUND UP!
Thursday, March 14, 2019
6:30 PM- 7:30 PM

WHO: Calling all Pre-K students and parents!

If you have a child who will be age 5 by August 1, 2019, we would like to invite you to the Kingsville Kindergarten Round-up.

Parents/Guardians are encouraged to bring along their pre-Kindergartener so that we may meet him or her. We suggest you to leave other children at home in order to make this night special for your pre-Kindergartner.

WHAT:
Information will be provided about Kindergarten screening and enrollment. Parents will be given the opportunity to sign their child up for the Kindergarten screening scheduled for April 12, 2019 and materials will be provided to parents in order to enhance the skills of pre-Kindergarteners prior to the upcoming school year.

Students will be allowed to spend time in the Kindergarten classroom and finish a simple Kindergarten activity while adults meet.

Where:
Kingsville Kindergarten Classroom

post_text: The last day to file as a candidate for the April 2nd election is Tuesday, January 15th. Candidate filing MUST be completed by 5 PM on the last day. It is recommended that you arrive 20-30 minutes prior to the 5PM deadline to ensure that all paperwork is completed prior to the deadline. One of the forms required for all candidates is the Form 5120 (Affidavit of Taxes Paid). This form can be accessed on the Department of Revenue website, completed and notarized, and taken with you to the appropriate filing location for the office you are seeking https://dor.mo.gov/forms/index.php?formName=5120&category_id=&year=99&sub. All other documents will need to be completed on site at the time of filing.
